2026-04-21 01:41:27 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['power supply module battery (12 V source)'] hypothesis_explanation='The control and load modules, their cabling, and the light‑sensor/bias networks have all been checked: relay remains closed when the sensor is forced dark, cabling polarity and continuity are correct, indicator and main lamps behave identically, and no individual control components appear faulty. The only persistent anomaly is that the overall circuit is reported as ‘unstable or oscillating’ with extremely small variations at the relay drive node, and all component‑level tests on the control side pass. Intermittent 0.5 s dropouts every ~20 s with no dependence on the timing or sensitivity settings are typical of a marginal or intermittently sagging supply, especially a weak or partially failing 12 V battery whose terminal voltage periodically dips under load and recovers. Because the power‑supply LED is referenced via a resistor directly across the source, it can remain apparently ON even when the supply droops just enough to momentarily drop the relay/lamp but not extinguish the LED. As all downstream circuitry has been cleared, the remaining credible root cause is the 12 V battery in the power supply module (or its immediate source connections) being faulty or unstable, so replacing/repairing the battery/source should resolve the periodic lamp dropouts.'
